01:10.520 --> 01:14.560
♪♪

01:14.560 --> 01:18.600
♪♪

01:18.600 --> 01:21.100
Yes, sir.

01:21.100 --> 01:22.640
Anything in the pool house?

01:22.640 --> 01:24.480
Possible traces of blood,
but not a lot.

01:24.480 --> 01:26.480
I told forensics
to put a rush on it.

01:26.480 --> 01:27.850
He looks older.

01:27.850 --> 01:29.350
He'd probably tell you

01:29.350 --> 01:30.770
the last eight years
have been tough on him.

01:30.770 --> 01:33.770
No more starring roles,
living off foreign endorsements.

01:33.770 --> 01:36.440
He killed two women
and got away with it...

01:36.440 --> 01:38.980
And he still gets to live
in this place.

01:40.730 --> 01:43.520
I need to make it right.

01:43.520 --> 01:45.400
If he killed Jessica,

01:45.400 --> 01:48.020
we're gonna put him away
this time... for good.

01:48.020 --> 01:49.600
You're damn right we are.

01:49.600 --> 01:57.600
♪♪

01:59.310 --> 02:01.060
Your retainer just cleared.

02:01.060 --> 02:05.270
$1.5 million's a hell
of a lot more than a retainer.

02:05.270 --> 02:06.940
The heads-up about
the search... that was for free.

02:06.940 --> 02:09.190
I didn't need a heads-up...
Mmhmm.

02:09.190 --> 02:10.600
And I have nothing to hide.

02:10.600 --> 02:13.940
So, uh... we're good?

02:13.940 --> 02:15.270
Yeah, we're good.

02:15.270 --> 02:18.060
Cops ain't gonna find anything.

02:18.060 --> 02:19.850
Fantastic.

02:19.850 --> 02:21.480
Stay put.

02:21.480 --> 02:24.230
I'm gonna go earn the big bucks.

02:24.230 --> 02:25.400
Hey, hey, hey!

02:25.400 --> 02:26.900
I want to see everything
that leaves this house.

02:26.900 --> 02:31.900
♪♪

02:31.900 --> 02:36.940
♪♪

02:36.940 --> 02:39.560
♪♪

02:39.560 --> 02:41.060
Hey.

02:41.060 --> 02:44.020
I can't talk to you
without your attorney present.

02:44.020 --> 02:46.770
Hey.
Why you doing this, huh?

02:46.770 --> 02:49.440
You lost, so what now?
You want revenge?

02:49.440 --> 02:50.810
You hate me for not
suffering enough?

02:50.810 --> 02:52.850
Is that it?
'Cause, believe me, I have.

02:52.850 --> 02:54.730
This isn't personal,
Mr. Johnson.

02:54.730 --> 02:56.100
It never has been.

02:56.100 --> 02:58.060
Right now the only thing
I care about is,

02:58.060 --> 03:00.940
did you kill Jessica Meyer?

03:00.940 --> 03:02.940
I... did... not.

03:02.940 --> 03:04.980
Then the evidence
will bear you out.

03:04.980 --> 03:06.850
Evidence doesn't lie.
People do.

03:06.850 --> 03:09.900
Hey!

03:09.900 --> 03:12.100
Hey, your investigator found
something in the little girl's room.

03:12.100 --> 03:13.560
What the hell you doing in Sunny's room?
Hey, relax, buddy.

03:13.560 --> 03:14.940
- Get your hands... She's a kid!
- Hey! Relax!

03:14.940 --> 03:17.640
Can you explain to your client
how a search warrant works?

03:17.640 --> 03:20.520
Keep her out of my daughter's room, man!
He's okay. He's okay. It's okay.

03:23.310 --> 03:25.060
I heard you found something
in the dollhouse attic.

03:25.060 --> 03:26.770
You need a light?

03:26.770 --> 03:28.400
I got one.

03:28.400 --> 03:36.400
♪♪

03:38.230 --> 03:40.690
♪♪

03:40.690 --> 03:43.980
Nice work, CJ.

03:43.980 --> 03:47.600
Cash, key, burner phone.

03:47.600 --> 03:50.140
Go Bag.

03:50.140 --> 03:51.770
Sevvy's ready to run.

03:51.770 --> 03:53.270
♪♪

03:56.230 --> 04:01.730
♪♪

04:01.730 --> 04:09.140
♪♪

04:10.350 --> 04:11.730
Okay.

04:11.730 --> 04:15.730
♪♪

04:18.730 --> 04:22.730
♪♪

04:28.520 --> 04:31.520
If he put the Go Bag together
before the murder,

04:31.520 --> 04:32.940
that would show premeditation.

04:32.940 --> 04:35.310
Well, my team is tracking
the cash and the car key,

04:35.310 --> 04:36.900
and LAPD's working
on the burner phone.

04:36.900 --> 04:38.600
You're back!

04:43.400 --> 04:45.400
We've been waiting
with bated breath.

04:45.400 --> 04:47.480
We have enough
to make an arrest?

04:47.480 --> 04:49.770
No one benefits
from dragging this out.

04:49.770 --> 04:52.600
But you benefit from getting it
over with quickly, right?

04:52.600 --> 04:55.400
You know what? As the D.A.,
I have to think about voters.

04:55.400 --> 04:56.690
That's a reality.

04:56.690 --> 04:57.850
I think we learned
eight years ago

04:57.850 --> 05:00.690
that a three-ring circus
isn't great for anyone.

05:00.690 --> 05:02.730
It'll take weeks to examine
what we found at the house.

05:02.730 --> 05:05.690
The Go Bag is incriminating,
but we're under a microscope.

05:05.690 --> 05:07.140
Even with the Jessica tapes,

05:07.140 --> 05:08.850
it's not enough
to make an arrest.

05:08.850 --> 05:11.190
Meanwhile, Ezra Wolf is selling
the public a B.S. story

05:11.190 --> 05:12.690
about Ben Mitchell,

05:12.690 --> 05:14.690
Jessica's personal-training
client, being the murderer.

05:14.690 --> 05:16.690
Bad luck for him
that he found her body.

05:16.690 --> 05:18.350
We need to counterattack.

05:18.350 --> 05:19.640
I'm gonna hold a press
conference,

05:19.640 --> 05:21.980
get it out there
that Sevvy was planning to flee.

05:21.980 --> 05:23.770
And then Wolf will twist
that into more B.S.

05:23.770 --> 05:27.350
about how the D.A.'s office
has a vendetta against Johnson.

05:27.350 --> 05:29.310
I'm not gonna sink
to Wolf's level.

05:29.310 --> 05:32.140
I try my case in court,
not the press.

05:32.140 --> 05:34.060
Our job is to follow
the evidence.

05:34.060 --> 05:35.730
So, you think we should
just sit back

05:35.730 --> 05:38.020
and let the public believe
Wolf's made-up story?

05:38.020 --> 05:40.640
The only story that matters
to us is Jessica's...

05:40.640 --> 05:43.520
What happened and why
and the proof of who did it.

05:43.520 --> 05:45.900
We only get one chance
to tell this story.

05:45.900 --> 05:47.600
We have to get it right.

05:47.600 --> 05:49.980
I understand all of that, but...
Maya's the lead on this.

05:49.980 --> 05:53.690
Isn't that what you decided,
Collier?

05:53.690 --> 05:55.980
- Right.
- Great.

05:55.980 --> 05:57.640
Then let her lead.

06:01.270 --> 06:03.440
I heard your car pull in.

06:03.440 --> 06:05.100
I was worried.

06:08.270 --> 06:10.480
- You okay?
- Yeah.

06:12.480 --> 06:16.060
♪♪

06:16.060 --> 06:18.020
I just wish all this
wasn't happening.

06:20.850 --> 06:22.850
Me, too.

06:25.600 --> 06:27.230
And the bag?

06:27.230 --> 06:28.900
I took care of it.

06:31.350 --> 06:33.020
Good boy.

06:36.440 --> 06:38.100
Did you look inside?

06:41.190 --> 06:43.350
I didn't... didn't
think that I should.

06:43.350 --> 06:50.770
♪♪

06:50.770 --> 06:53.480
Listen, Wolf wants to plan
something for tomorrow,

06:53.480 --> 06:56.270
wants me to take you guys out
for brunch,

06:56.270 --> 06:58.230
show the public
that we're a happy family,

06:58.230 --> 07:00.770
that my children believe in me.

07:00.770 --> 07:02.440
Whatever you need,
I'll be there.

07:02.440 --> 07:10.440
♪♪

07:10.810 --> 07:13.060
Hey, Dad.

07:13.060 --> 07:14.770
It's gonna be okay.

07:18.100 --> 07:20.480
I should be the one
telling you that.

07:20.480 --> 07:28.480
♪♪

07:34.060 --> 07:36.020
- You asked for me?
- Yeah.

07:36.020 --> 07:38.600
I'm gonna need you to be
the liaison with forensics.

07:38.600 --> 07:42.600
We can't wait six weeks to get
the DNA from the Johnson house.

07:42.600 --> 07:44.730
I hope you don't mind that
I disagreed with you earlier.

07:44.730 --> 07:46.980
Not at all.
We're a team.

07:46.980 --> 07:48.940
You should speak your mind.

07:48.940 --> 07:50.190
You mean that?
Yeah.

07:52.480 --> 07:54.100
Okay.

07:54.100 --> 07:56.600
I should be lead on this case.

07:56.600 --> 08:00.480
The only thing you bring
that I don't is baggage.

08:00.480 --> 08:03.230
Anything else?
Yes.

08:03.230 --> 08:06.350
Since you like stories, here's
the one Wolf is going to tell...

08:06.350 --> 08:08.600
Vengeful white lady
comes back to town

08:08.600 --> 08:11.060
to persecute innocent black man.

08:11.060 --> 08:14.100
If Matthew didn't have a crush
on you, he'd see that.

08:14.100 --> 08:16.690
This should be my case,

08:16.690 --> 08:18.440
not just because
I'm a person of color

08:18.440 --> 08:21.770
and it's 2019 and optics matter

08:21.770 --> 08:24.310
but because I'm
a better lawyer than you

08:24.310 --> 08:28.310
and I know we can't beat
Ezra Wolf from the high road.

08:28.310 --> 08:30.190
Thanks for sharing.

08:35.730 --> 08:39.230
Is she right?

08:39.230 --> 08:42.230
She's not a better lawyer
than you.

08:42.230 --> 08:50.230
♪♪

08:50.560 --> 08:51.690
What you got for me?

08:51.690 --> 08:53.020
Reuben.

08:53.020 --> 08:54.900
Double sauce.

08:54.900 --> 08:56.060
My man.

08:56.060 --> 08:57.850
I got your back, my friend.

08:57.850 --> 09:00.850
You got time to chitchat,

09:00.850 --> 09:02.770
or are you cutting straight to the chase?
Straight to the chase.

09:02.770 --> 09:04.490
I know you didn't call me here
for a picnic.

09:06.140 --> 09:09.270
Spent the day tailing
Ben Mitchell, like you asked me.

09:09.270 --> 09:11.310
And this is where he landed?
Not quite.

09:15.690 --> 09:17.190
Edify me.

09:17.190 --> 09:20.350
Well, why tell when I can show?

09:20.350 --> 09:26.060
♪♪

09:26.060 --> 09:31.940
♪♪

09:31.940 --> 09:33.060
The car key from the Go Bag

09:33.060 --> 09:35.310
is a 2013 Lexus IS.

09:35.310 --> 09:36.690
Can you tie it to Johnson?

09:36.690 --> 09:37.770
That's what I'm working on.

09:38.940 --> 09:41.520
You need to see this.

09:41.520 --> 09:44.230
Thank you all for coming out.
This will be fast.

09:44.230 --> 09:47.350
While the D.A.'s office was on
a search-and-destroy mission

09:47.350 --> 09:48.900
at the house of an innocent man,

09:48.900 --> 09:50.480
they let the real killer,

09:50.480 --> 09:52.640
Ben Mitchell,
dispose of evidence.

09:52.640 --> 09:55.270
But my investigator
was here to see it.

09:55.270 --> 10:00.730
♪♪

10:00.730 --> 10:04.560
This is what Ben Mitchell
wanted to hide...

10:04.560 --> 10:06.690
A necklace belonging
to his victim,

10:06.690 --> 10:08.310
Jessica Meyer.

10:08.310 --> 10:10.980
It's in that Dumpster right now.

10:10.980 --> 10:12.690
That's right.

10:12.690 --> 10:15.560
I'm doing your job for you,
Maya.

10:15.560 --> 10:17.900
If you won't look
for the real killer,

10:17.900 --> 10:19.310
then I will.

10:25.980 --> 10:32.440
♪♪

10:32.440 --> 10:33.760
Wanna know where
I just came from?

10:35.140 --> 10:36.640
Cher's house.

10:36.640 --> 10:38.900
She was about to sing "Believe."

10:38.900 --> 10:40.440
I love that song.

10:40.440 --> 10:42.730
But I had to leave
'cause you all screwed up.

10:42.730 --> 10:45.060
Alan... What the
ever-loving hell happened?!

10:45.060 --> 10:47.480
Wolf had a tail on Ben Mitchell.
I got that.

10:47.480 --> 10:48.770
Why didn't we have a tail
on him?

10:48.770 --> 10:50.640
Detectives interviewed
Mitchell three times.

10:50.640 --> 10:52.060
They didn't think he was
a factor in the case,

10:52.060 --> 10:54.190
and neither did we.

10:54.190 --> 10:55.770
What about this beauty?

10:55.770 --> 10:58.140
Ben and Jessica partying it up?

10:58.140 --> 11:01.310
Our office is being
out-investigated by Ezra Wolf.

11:01.310 --> 11:04.140
He's killing us in the press.
He's winning right now.

11:04.140 --> 11:06.690
Do you know how bad
this looks for me?

11:06.690 --> 11:08.350
Where are you going?!

11:08.350 --> 11:10.270
I'm gonna talk to Ben Mitchell
before the press does,

11:10.270 --> 11:12.060
which I would have done already

11:12.060 --> 11:14.640
if we didn't have to wait
for you to get back from Cher's.

11:17.310 --> 11:18.850
What she said.

11:22.230 --> 11:24.100
Loni, would you shut the door
on your way out?

11:26.520 --> 11:28.690
Collier.

11:28.690 --> 11:31.020
You know who else
was at the party?

11:31.020 --> 11:33.060
Elton John?

11:33.060 --> 11:36.100
Talar Petrossian.

11:36.100 --> 11:37.810
She said you had lunch with her.

11:37.810 --> 11:39.230
She's an old friend.

11:39.230 --> 11:41.640
She's a big-league fundraiser.

11:41.640 --> 11:43.560
I think I'm starting to see
your sudden hankering

11:43.560 --> 11:46.350
for press conferences.

11:46.350 --> 11:49.520
You want the exposure
'cause you want my job.

11:49.520 --> 11:51.100
Talar reached out to me.

11:53.230 --> 11:54.940
I'm just keeping
my options open.

11:57.520 --> 11:58.640
Just to be clear,

11:58.640 --> 12:01.480
if there's any face
in front of a camera,

12:01.480 --> 12:03.520
it's me.

12:03.520 --> 12:06.400
♪♪

12:08.400 --> 12:15.520
♪♪

12:15.520 --> 12:17.400
So far, Ben Mitchell has not...

12:17.400 --> 12:19.020
Oh, there's
Ms. Travis right now.

12:21.440 --> 12:23.690
- Maya! -Real quick, please.
- One second, please. Maya!

12:23.690 --> 12:26.020
Are you ready to press charges yet?
Is Ben Mitchell a suspect?

12:26.020 --> 12:28.020
Ben Mitchell's a witness,
nothing more.

12:28.020 --> 12:29.940
Maya, are you here
to make an arrest?

12:29.940 --> 12:31.940
- No comment.
- Is Sevvy Johnson innocent?

12:31.940 --> 12:34.270
- No comment.
- Were Ben and Jessica lovers?

12:34.270 --> 12:35.560
- No comment.
- Why did he do it?

12:35.560 --> 12:38.140
Respect his privacy, please,
and back up!

12:38.140 --> 12:40.020
Excuse me.

12:47.640 --> 12:49.940
Mr. Mitchell, I'm Maya... Just come in.
Just come in.

12:53.400 --> 12:55.940
I didn't kill Jessica.
Ezra Wolf is a liar.

12:55.940 --> 12:57.770
Would you like some water?
We're not in a rush.

12:57.770 --> 12:59.640
He keeps saying I killed her.

12:59.640 --> 13:01.270
I can't even go to the office.

13:01.270 --> 13:03.690
The way people
are looking at me...

13:03.690 --> 13:07.020
Mr. Mitchell, we do have
to ask you about the necklace.

13:07.020 --> 13:08.730
Would you like to sit down?

13:08.730 --> 13:11.640
Was the necklace Jessica's?

13:11.640 --> 13:13.190
Um...

13:13.190 --> 13:15.440
A couple weeks ago, a-after
one of our training sessions,

13:15.440 --> 13:17.140
I noticed it on the ground.

13:17.140 --> 13:19.140
It must've fallen off,
so I took it home.

13:19.140 --> 13:22.560
I was gonna return it to her,
and then...

13:22.560 --> 13:24.230
that day, I...

13:24.230 --> 13:26.810
The day you found her body?

13:26.810 --> 13:29.520
When I, um...
When I found her... like that,

13:29.520 --> 13:31.190
I, uh...

13:36.440 --> 13:37.940
You already spoke to the police
on the scene.

13:37.940 --> 13:40.400
Why didn't you tell them
about the necklace?

13:40.400 --> 13:43.310
Well, I...
I d... I didn't think about it

13:43.310 --> 13:46.850
until Ezra Wolf told the world
I'm a murderer.

13:46.850 --> 13:48.440
I just... I-I-I panicked.

13:48.440 --> 13:49.940
I remembered it was
in my gym bag,

13:49.940 --> 13:52.310
and all I could think was,
"Get rid of it."

13:52.310 --> 13:55.140
I know it makes me look bad,
but I-I...

13:55.140 --> 13:57.900
I didn't kill her.

13:57.900 --> 14:01.230
I should tell you, I...

14:01.230 --> 14:04.640
I deleted a photo of me and Jess
from my Instagram account.

14:04.640 --> 14:05.770
We're aware of the photo.

14:08.940 --> 14:11.310
Did you and Jessica
hang out a lot?

14:11.310 --> 14:13.350
No.
Only that once.

14:13.350 --> 14:15.350
I knew the press was gonna be
all over anything about her,

14:15.350 --> 14:16.850
and I'm a private person.

14:16.850 --> 14:19.020
I didn't want
to be hounded by them.

14:19.020 --> 14:21.600
And now I-I-I... I can't even go
to the grocery store.

14:21.600 --> 14:23.940
I feel like the whole world
hates me.

14:23.940 --> 14:25.310
Will it ever end?

14:25.310 --> 14:27.520
If can clear you
of Jessica's murder,

14:27.520 --> 14:29.310
this will fade.

14:29.310 --> 14:32.400
People will move on
to someone else.

14:32.400 --> 14:34.350
But how long will that take?

14:34.350 --> 14:36.100
I don't know.

14:36.100 --> 14:38.600
But you'll get through this.

14:38.600 --> 14:40.520
You will.

14:40.520 --> 14:46.730
♪♪

14:46.730 --> 14:52.900
♪♪

14:52.900 --> 14:56.100
Ding dong.
It's Uncle Ezra...

14:56.100 --> 14:58.640
a.k.a.
your personal chauffeur.

14:58.640 --> 15:02.140
It's time for brunch
with your dad.

15:02.140 --> 15:05.140
I told Ares I wasn't going
to the brunch today.

15:05.140 --> 15:07.730
Oh, right.
Yeah, he did mention that.

15:09.980 --> 15:12.900
You look tired.
You haven't been sleeping well?

15:12.900 --> 15:15.520
I don't think anyone
in my family is sleeping much.

15:15.520 --> 15:16.980
Mm.

15:16.980 --> 15:20.520
But maybe... just maybe...

15:20.520 --> 15:23.730
You have a guilty conscience.

15:23.730 --> 15:25.900
I read the search warrant.

15:25.900 --> 15:28.310
Maya Travis got probable cause
to search your dad's house

15:28.310 --> 15:31.350
from a storage locker
belonging to an "unnamed CI."

15:35.190 --> 15:38.190
Yeah. I put
the pieces together.

15:40.100 --> 15:42.020
Are you gonna tell my dad?

15:46.060 --> 15:47.440
Nah.

15:47.440 --> 15:49.400
I know how
the prosecution works.

15:49.400 --> 15:51.060
They'll say anything
to get what they want.

15:51.060 --> 15:54.350
Me?
I'm on your side.

15:54.350 --> 15:55.690
Okay.

15:55.690 --> 15:59.060
I've known you since you were
13 years old.

15:59.060 --> 16:00.400
I know you wouldn't abandon
your dad

16:00.400 --> 16:02.140
when he needs you the most.

16:02.140 --> 16:03.270
Right?

16:05.600 --> 16:07.770
- Yeah.
- Okay, then.

16:07.770 --> 16:10.690
Now, as long as you play
your part,

16:10.690 --> 16:13.440
you smile for the camera,

16:13.440 --> 16:15.230
we'll keep this
our little secret.

16:15.230 --> 16:20.600
♪♪

16:20.600 --> 16:22.480
Come on. Everybody's
getting ready at your dad's.

16:22.480 --> 16:24.810
Ares has picked out
a nice dress for you.

16:24.810 --> 16:27.270
Something yellow, I think.

16:27.270 --> 16:29.810
You'll look like sunshine.

16:32.810 --> 16:35.690
We create reality, okay?

16:35.690 --> 16:37.810
People don't know what to
believe, so we tell them, okay?

16:37.810 --> 16:40.640
We all know what a close-knit,
deeply loving family you are,

16:40.640 --> 16:43.190
but we need the public
to know that, too.

16:43.190 --> 16:47.980
So, to that end, I have chosen
your brunch spot carefully

16:47.980 --> 16:49.480
to maximize exposure.

16:49.480 --> 16:51.690
All you need to do
is be yourselves

16:51.690 --> 16:55.230
and let social-media nature
take its course.

16:55.230 --> 16:57.140
Needless to say,
it is imperative

16:57.140 --> 17:01.100
that you be the absolute best
versions of yourselves, okay?

17:01.100 --> 17:02.400
Do smile.

17:02.400 --> 17:03.440
Do touch each other
affectionately.

17:03.440 --> 17:06.560
Do not talk to reporters

17:06.560 --> 17:09.190
or let yourselves
be provoked by paparazzi.

17:09.190 --> 17:10.349
♪ Girl, I see you ♪

17:10.349 --> 17:12.230
- Deal.
- Gotcha.

17:15.770 --> 17:19.099
That? The pacing
and the hunched body language?

17:19.099 --> 17:20.520
Screams guilty.

17:20.520 --> 17:23.480
Yeah, I need relaxed bodies,
soft shoulders.

17:23.480 --> 17:27.060
You're an actor.
You can manage that, right?

17:27.060 --> 17:29.560
Yeah.
I can manage that.

17:29.560 --> 17:31.400
Star! You're here.

17:31.400 --> 17:32.850
Let's get you dressed.

17:32.850 --> 17:36.100
Hello, darling.

17:36.100 --> 17:37.560
What's going on
with Ben Mitchell?

17:37.560 --> 17:39.350
The prosecution talked
to him last night,

17:39.350 --> 17:40.850
so now we just sit tight

17:40.850 --> 17:42.900
and wait for him
to make his next dumb move.

17:42.900 --> 17:44.810
So we can cancel
this stupid photo op.

17:44.810 --> 17:46.730
We don't need to do it
if Mitchell's gonna be arrested,

17:46.730 --> 17:48.350
do we? Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, pardner.

17:48.350 --> 17:49.600
You're getting way ahead
of yourself.

17:49.600 --> 17:51.600
He just threw away a necklace.
That's all.

17:51.600 --> 17:53.310
No.
You said he killed her.

17:53.310 --> 17:55.350
I say a lot of things.

17:55.350 --> 17:57.730
I mean, you can't afford
to buy into my hype.

17:57.730 --> 17:59.210
You have to keep your eye
on the ball.

18:03.140 --> 18:06.270
You still think I did it.

18:06.270 --> 18:08.640
It doesn't matter what I think.

18:10.900 --> 18:13.640
Just play the game.

18:13.640 --> 18:15.270
Enjoy the eggs Benedict.

18:15.270 --> 18:23.270
♪♪

18:23.310 --> 18:26.100
Ben Mitchell said Jessica
was already dead

18:26.100 --> 18:28.140
when he arrived
for his training session.

18:28.140 --> 18:29.850
Did the responding officers

18:29.850 --> 18:32.270
sense anything off with him?
No.

18:32.270 --> 18:34.770
And they tested his hands
and his clothes?

18:34.770 --> 18:37.190
No blood spatter,
no fingerprints on the murder weapon.

18:37.190 --> 18:41.060
Everything says Ben Mitchell
didn't kill her,

18:41.060 --> 18:44.980
but why do I feel like I have
to save him from Ezra Wolf?

18:44.980 --> 18:46.440
Hero complex?

18:48.560 --> 18:51.060
Here's what I don't get.
Okay, this is a popular beach,

18:51.060 --> 18:52.850
even at that time
of the morning.

18:52.850 --> 18:55.060
Nobody saw anything?

18:55.060 --> 18:57.640
Cops interviewed all the
beach bums and surfer dudes,

18:57.640 --> 18:59.560
fitness freaks.

18:59.560 --> 19:01.940
So far, no luck.

19:01.940 --> 19:04.480
I got to take this.

19:04.480 --> 19:08.060
Hi.

19:11.400 --> 19:12.940
I promise.

19:12.940 --> 19:15.600
No.
You're gonna be fine.

19:18.100 --> 19:19.600
Mm-hmm.

19:19.600 --> 19:21.600
I love you.

19:21.600 --> 19:23.350
There was a bonfire
down the beach.

19:23.350 --> 19:25.190
Maybe there was a party

19:25.190 --> 19:26.730
the night before
Jessica was killed.

19:26.730 --> 19:28.100
Those things can go late.

19:28.100 --> 19:29.480
Do you have any friends

19:29.480 --> 19:30.980
that work in Malibu
private security?

19:30.980 --> 19:32.640
One or two.

19:32.640 --> 19:34.960
They might tell me something
that they won't tell the cops.

19:36.900 --> 19:38.690
So...

19:38.690 --> 19:41.310
was that your boyfriend
on the phone?

19:41.310 --> 19:43.520
Husband?

19:43.520 --> 19:46.560
Do you have a husband now? No, Maya.
I have an ex-husband...

19:46.560 --> 19:48.230
Soon-to-be...

19:48.230 --> 19:50.900
And I have a daughter, Maya.

19:50.900 --> 19:52.310
She's 6.

19:52.310 --> 19:54.270
Oh, my God.
I didn't know.

19:54.270 --> 19:55.520
Well, it's been
eight years, Maya.

19:55.520 --> 19:57.100
There's a lot you don't know.

19:57.100 --> 20:01.850
No phone calls, no texts,
not even a Christmas card.

20:01.850 --> 20:04.440
I don't know you anymore, Maya,
and you sure as hell don't know me.

20:04.440 --> 20:06.100
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean...

20:06.100 --> 20:07.850
Well, of course
you didn't mean it.

20:07.850 --> 20:10.520
You were just thinking about you
and your feelings, but...

20:10.520 --> 20:13.140
you know that thing
that Maya Angelou says...

20:13.140 --> 20:16.730
When someone shows you
who they are, believe them?

20:16.730 --> 20:19.140
When the going gets rough,
you are someone who leaves.

20:19.140 --> 20:20.980
You have no idea

20:20.980 --> 20:22.810
what it felt like to be me
eight years ago.

20:22.810 --> 20:24.690
Okay.

20:24.690 --> 20:27.850
Was your face on the news
all day, every day?

20:27.850 --> 20:29.980
Was your entire life
dissected...

20:29.980 --> 20:31.400
Your hair, your clothes,

20:31.400 --> 20:35.100
every single decision,
every mistake?

20:35.100 --> 20:37.560
Nobody knows your name.

20:37.560 --> 20:42.560
Nobody blames you for letting
a murderer walk.

20:42.560 --> 20:45.140
You know what? You're right.
We're not friends anymore.

20:45.140 --> 20:46.980
We just work together.

20:50.770 --> 20:53.060
What the hell?

20:53.060 --> 20:55.560
The car key we found
in Sunny Johnson's bedroom.

20:55.560 --> 20:58.440
The registration came back
to Ben Mitchell?

20:58.440 --> 21:00.520
We thought the Go Bag
was Sevvy's.

21:00.520 --> 21:03.100
What if it was Jessica's?

21:03.100 --> 21:04.900
She was the one
who was planning to run.

21:04.900 --> 21:06.640
And Ben Mitchell
was helping her leave.

21:06.640 --> 21:08.520
He lied to us.

21:14.310 --> 21:15.900
♪ You already know it's us ♪

21:15.900 --> 21:18.140
♪ Always got more,
I could never get enough ♪

21:18.140 --> 21:21.060
♪ Life's short, oh, well... it,
I'ma live it up ♪

21:21.060 --> 21:22.770
♪ Fast car, NASCAR ♪
How are you?

21:22.770 --> 21:24.230
♪ Hop in, then I fell in love ♪

21:24.230 --> 21:27.140
♪ Jaguar, Aston, you know
I'ma buy me one ♪

21:27.140 --> 21:29.980
♪ Rock star lifestyle,
yeah, I live the lifestyle ♪

21:29.980 --> 21:32.100
♪ Monster, monster when
all of the lights out ♪

21:32.100 --> 21:33.900
Coming?

21:33.900 --> 21:35.400
♪ Yellow bone, red bone,
Binyah Binyah polliwog ♪

21:35.400 --> 21:38.600
This just feels so wrong.

21:38.600 --> 21:40.980
Jessica's dead,
and we're doing a photo op?

21:43.440 --> 21:45.900
I get that you're upset.

21:45.900 --> 21:47.980
We're all upset.

21:47.980 --> 21:49.600
But he's our dad,
and he needs us.

21:49.600 --> 21:52.310
You've always idolized him,

21:52.310 --> 21:53.730
even when you were a kid,

21:53.730 --> 21:56.190
but, Gabe, it's time to grow up.

21:56.190 --> 21:59.440
He's always been there for me,
even when I had no one.

22:01.480 --> 22:03.690
Yeah.

22:03.690 --> 22:06.190
Well...

22:06.190 --> 22:07.980
he's not as great
as you think he is.

22:14.850 --> 22:16.850
How are you feeling about all of this?
Why'd you lawyer up?

22:16.850 --> 22:18.230
Is the D.A.
going to charge you?

22:18.230 --> 22:20.560
Were you Jessica's lover?
Did you kill Jessica?

22:20.560 --> 22:22.310
Ben Mitchell didn't kill anyone.

22:22.310 --> 22:23.480
- No further comment.
- Did you kill her?

22:23.480 --> 22:25.080
What was the nature
of your relationship?

22:28.640 --> 22:31.230
Mitchell's on his way up.
You ready?

22:31.230 --> 22:34.140
Let him stew.

22:34.140 --> 22:35.850
- You want me in the interview?
- No, thanks.

22:35.850 --> 22:38.230
I asked Detective North to join.

22:38.230 --> 22:44.020
♪♪

22:46.770 --> 22:48.520
The customers are getting
in the game.

22:48.520 --> 22:51.440
I've got three tweets,
four Instagram posts,

22:51.440 --> 22:54.140
and the table on the right
just started a live video feed.

22:54.140 --> 22:56.020
We are on the way
to critical mass.

22:56.020 --> 22:57.850
- Excellent.
- Got you your favorite...

22:57.850 --> 23:00.980
Chocolate chip with banana.
Thanks, Daddy.

23:00.980 --> 23:02.400
There you go, darling.

23:04.730 --> 23:06.400
Junior,
you speak to your brother?

23:06.400 --> 23:07.400
Mm-hmm.

23:07.400 --> 23:08.850
How was his trip back to school?

23:08.850 --> 23:10.520
Oh, he's good.
Flight was on time.

23:10.520 --> 23:12.480
He scored an aisle seat.

23:12.480 --> 23:14.690
Hey, did you catch that game
last night?

23:14.690 --> 23:16.100
No, I missed it.

23:16.100 --> 23:17.730
We've got another live feed.

23:17.730 --> 23:20.440
How 'bout you, son?
You working this weekend?

23:20.440 --> 23:22.640
Tell Star to scoot left.
Bring Sunny down for a quick lesson.

23:22.640 --> 23:24.480
Hear that, Sunny? Hmm?
Scoot to your left.

23:24.480 --> 23:26.190
The table behind you
is live-streaming.

23:26.190 --> 23:34.190
♪♪

23:34.270 --> 23:36.770
Star, it's been a while since
you've been over the house.

23:36.770 --> 23:39.900
Sunny was hoping you could
come over and have a swim.

23:39.900 --> 23:42.230
Oh, not today.
I'm sorry, Sunny.

23:42.230 --> 23:44.270
It's okay.

23:44.270 --> 23:46.690
Maybe time, huh?
Yeah.

23:46.690 --> 23:49.230
I feel sick.

23:49.230 --> 23:50.600
I'm gonna take a car home.

23:52.690 --> 23:55.100
- Where is she going?
- No, Star.

23:55.100 --> 23:57.730
Star!

23:58.850 --> 24:00.440
Star, what are you doing here?

24:00.440 --> 24:01.690
What's the story with your father?
My daughter is grieving

24:01.690 --> 24:03.730
her friend.

24:03.730 --> 24:06.690
She has a right
to do that in peace.

24:06.690 --> 24:09.140
This was Jessica's
favorite restaurant.

24:09.140 --> 24:11.190
We came here today to
honor her memory... Oh, no.

24:11.190 --> 24:12.770
- No.
- No.

24:12.770 --> 24:14.600
As a family.
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

24:14.600 --> 24:18.520
I would appreciate
if you could respect it.

24:18.520 --> 24:21.400
The LAPD served a search warrant
on your house yesterday.

24:21.400 --> 24:23.020
Any comment?
No comment.

24:23.020 --> 24:25.190
Don... You have no comment.

24:25.190 --> 24:32.440
♪♪

24:32.440 --> 24:34.350
I want the police to find

24:34.350 --> 24:37.060
the monster that killed Jessica.

24:37.060 --> 24:40.190
And if searching the home that
we shared helps them do that,

24:40.190 --> 24:42.520
then I'm all for it.

24:42.520 --> 24:45.900
They know that they have
my complete cooperation

24:45.900 --> 24:47.980
and that I will do
whatever it takes

24:47.980 --> 24:49.730
to get justice for Jessica.

24:49.730 --> 24:56.850
♪♪

24:56.850 --> 24:58.810
Oh, he's good.

24:58.810 --> 25:00.730
Yeah.

25:00.730 --> 25:02.520
He's good.

25:02.520 --> 25:05.350
Why didn't you tell us
you bought Jessica a car?

25:05.350 --> 25:08.980
Or that you emptied your savings
account to give her $50,000?

25:08.980 --> 25:11.850
I should have, I wanted to,
but I was scared.

25:11.850 --> 25:14.020
I thought if I just kept quiet,
it would all go away.

25:14.020 --> 25:15.560
That's a lot of money
to give somebody

25:15.560 --> 25:17.020
who's just your trainer.

25:17.020 --> 25:18.640
I had to help her
get away from him.

25:18.640 --> 25:20.480
- From Sevvy Johnson?
- He hurt her.

25:20.480 --> 25:23.520
I saw the bruises.
You need to check this out.

25:26.810 --> 25:30.810
♪♪

25:30.810 --> 25:32.310
What the hell is that?

25:32.310 --> 25:34.440
No idea.

25:34.440 --> 25:40.850
♪♪

25:40.850 --> 25:43.730
- "I'm worried about you.
- You need to leave him."

25:43.730 --> 25:45.690
"Why won't you answer my calls?

25:45.690 --> 25:47.140
He's no good for you."

25:47.140 --> 25:49.600
Sound familiar?

25:49.600 --> 25:50.850
"You're a liar and a user!

25:50.850 --> 25:53.940
I'm not going to let you
do this to me."

25:53.940 --> 25:56.850
These are the texts we found
on Jessica's burner phone.

25:56.850 --> 25:58.980
They're all from you.

25:58.980 --> 26:00.190
And here's the last one you sent

26:00.190 --> 26:01.810
the night before
she was murdered...

26:01.810 --> 26:04.810
"You took me for all I had.
You played me this whole time.

26:04.810 --> 26:07.100
You deserve what you get,
you bitch!"

26:07.100 --> 26:08.270
That's it.
We're done here.

26:08.270 --> 26:09.690
She could've been with me.

26:09.690 --> 26:12.770
I did everything for her,
and she still chose him!

26:12.770 --> 26:14.350
This whole thing is her fault!
Stop!

26:14.350 --> 26:15.560
Next time you want to see him,

26:15.560 --> 26:16.850
you better have
an arrest warrant.

26:16.850 --> 26:18.850
Don't leave town!

26:18.850 --> 26:24.400
♪♪

26:29.480 --> 26:31.980
It can't be Ben Mitchell.

26:31.980 --> 26:33.270
I know.

26:33.270 --> 26:34.690
It wasn't supposed
to go this way.

26:36.940 --> 26:38.900
I don't want it to be him.

26:38.900 --> 26:41.310
From the moment
I saw you on my porch,

26:41.310 --> 26:43.350
I could see the story
in my head,

26:43.350 --> 26:46.980
and it always ended
with Sevvy Johnson behind bars.

26:46.980 --> 26:48.600
That's why I brought you here...

26:48.600 --> 26:51.440
So we could finally bring him
to justice together.

26:53.850 --> 26:55.730
He killed two women.

26:55.730 --> 26:58.600
He abused Jessica.
We know that.

26:58.600 --> 27:00.600
How can it be Ben Mitchell?!

27:00.600 --> 27:06.100
♪♪

27:06.100 --> 27:08.560
I want revenge.

27:08.560 --> 27:10.140
I do.

27:12.190 --> 27:15.520
I want to see Sevvy Johnson rot.

27:20.350 --> 27:24.140
This was my one chance
to make it right

27:24.140 --> 27:25.980
and it's gone.

27:25.980 --> 27:33.560
♪♪

27:42.730 --> 27:44.100
Well, there she is...

27:44.100 --> 27:46.560
The prosecutress
with the mostess.

27:46.560 --> 27:48.350
I was beginning to think
you didn't like me.

27:48.350 --> 27:51.020
I just walked up
10 flights in heels.

27:51.020 --> 27:52.520
What do you want?

27:52.520 --> 27:55.400
The whole smorgasbord.

27:55.400 --> 27:57.560
What you found in Sevvy's house,

27:57.560 --> 27:59.600
what's going on
with Ben Mitchell... all of it.

27:59.600 --> 28:01.850
No.

28:04.020 --> 28:05.690
No?

28:05.690 --> 28:08.560
I am done talking to you.
It was a mistake.

28:08.560 --> 28:12.020
What's with the sudden attack
of conscience?

28:12.020 --> 28:15.060
I was pissed off that Maya took my
case, and I wanted to hurt her.

28:15.060 --> 28:17.400
Uh-huh.
I can do stupid, impulsive things

28:17.400 --> 28:20.190
when I'm pissed off.
And now you want backsies.

28:20.190 --> 28:22.060
This is not fourth grade.

28:22.060 --> 28:23.770
It's not the way it works.

28:23.770 --> 28:25.690
I call, you jump,

28:25.690 --> 28:27.350
and you tell me
what I want to know.

28:27.350 --> 28:30.520
Or my next call will be
to the D.A., Alan Wiest,

28:30.520 --> 28:32.980
and then you can
kiss your job and your bar card

28:32.980 --> 28:35.230
and your career
as a lawyer goodbye.

28:39.770 --> 28:41.810
It was worth a shot.
Mm-hmm.

28:41.810 --> 28:43.690
I thought maybe you had
a shred of decency.

28:43.690 --> 28:45.230
Surprise!

28:48.770 --> 28:50.980
We found a Go Bag.
Mm-hmm.

28:50.980 --> 28:53.690
Cash, car keys, cellphone.

28:53.690 --> 28:57.440
We thought it was Sevvy's.
It wasn't.

28:57.440 --> 28:59.230
Let's just say things
don't look good for Mitchell.

28:59.230 --> 29:01.690
Oh.

29:01.690 --> 29:04.020
Thank you.

29:04.020 --> 29:05.480
And try wedges.

29:05.480 --> 29:08.690
My ex-wives say
they're kinder to the feet.

29:08.690 --> 29:15.270
♪♪

29:15.270 --> 29:17.480
Hey.
Hey.

29:17.480 --> 29:20.140
You okay?

29:22.770 --> 29:24.690
I was worried.

29:24.690 --> 29:26.600
I'm fine.

29:26.600 --> 29:29.640
Wolf called.

29:29.640 --> 29:32.770
Yeah.

29:34.440 --> 29:36.730
Looks like they're gonna
arrest Ben Mitchell,

29:36.730 --> 29:39.060
maybe by tonight.

29:39.060 --> 29:40.520
Yeah.

29:40.520 --> 29:43.480
That'll be a relief
to Jessica's parents.

29:43.480 --> 29:45.360
I'll give them a call
and see how they're doing.

29:47.350 --> 29:49.850
Dad.
I need...

29:49.850 --> 29:51.310
you to believe in me, Star.

29:54.400 --> 29:56.440
You said yourself
they're gonna arrest that guy...

29:56.440 --> 29:58.690
Star.

29:58.690 --> 30:00.560
Talk to me.

30:00.560 --> 30:08.480
♪♪

30:08.480 --> 30:10.440
I know you used to hit Mom.

30:14.560 --> 30:16.560
I remember.

30:16.560 --> 30:23.100
♪♪

30:23.100 --> 30:26.020
I made a lot of mistakes
in my life, baby.

30:26.020 --> 30:28.600
And for many reasons,
I was an angry man back then,

30:28.600 --> 30:31.770
but that's not who I am
anymore, darling.

30:31.770 --> 30:34.730
Did you ever hurt Jessica?

30:34.730 --> 30:39.690
♪♪

30:39.690 --> 30:41.060
Never.

30:41.060 --> 30:49.060
♪♪

30:49.100 --> 30:52.190
I believe you.

30:55.640 --> 30:57.850
I believe you.

30:57.850 --> 30:59.600
I believe you, Dad.

30:59.600 --> 31:07.600
♪♪

31:08.810 --> 31:14.940
♪♪

31:14.940 --> 31:16.350
I had an "aha" moment.

31:18.850 --> 31:20.350
The reason
you were so determined

31:20.350 --> 31:22.270
to bring Maya
back for this case.

31:25.560 --> 31:27.850
You're covering your ass.

31:27.850 --> 31:30.400
You want her to take the hit if
this thing turns into a crapshow,

31:30.400 --> 31:32.770
which it is rapidly doing.

31:32.770 --> 31:35.560
I would never throw one of my
lawyers under the bus.

31:35.560 --> 31:36.640
Right.

31:38.900 --> 31:40.440
Right. Right.

31:42.770 --> 31:44.400
I figured it out.

31:44.400 --> 31:46.190
How long 'til Maya
figures it out, too?

31:46.190 --> 31:52.640
♪♪

31:52.640 --> 31:55.060
Murder suspect Ben Mitchell,
a former I.T. consultant

31:55.060 --> 31:56.940
for Horizon Platform Solutions,

31:56.940 --> 32:00.400
is reportedly holed up here
in his Woodland Hills home.

32:00.400 --> 32:03.140
Mitchell was a personal-training
client of Jessica Meyer,

32:03.140 --> 32:06.440
who was murdered
approximately a week ago.

32:06.440 --> 32:08.730
While the prosecution
has declined to comment,

32:08.730 --> 32:10.850
there is speculation
that Mitchell was obsessed

32:10.850 --> 32:12.440
with the victim.

32:12.440 --> 32:16.190
Sources close to the case
say an arrest is imminent.

32:16.190 --> 32:18.230
Wolf and his defense team
had been tracking

32:18.230 --> 32:20.270
Ben Mitchell early on

32:20.270 --> 32:22.100
after it was revealed
he discovered

32:22.100 --> 32:24.230
Jessica Meyer's body.

32:24.230 --> 32:26.690
Stylist Lindsay Berg,
who briefly dated Mitchell

32:26.690 --> 32:29.270
after they met
on a popular dating app.

32:29.270 --> 32:31.850
We had coffee.
He was super awkward.

32:31.850 --> 32:34.850
He kind of had that
serial-killer vibe, you know?

32:34.850 --> 32:36.900
Movie star Sevvy Johnson,
who had been considered...

32:36.900 --> 32:38.520
We may have a witness.

32:38.520 --> 32:39.770
Who is it?

32:39.770 --> 32:41.350
This kid who was at
the bonfire party

32:41.350 --> 32:43.350
the night
before Jessica was killed.

32:43.350 --> 32:45.190
My guy at Malibu Home Security

32:45.190 --> 32:46.600
said most of the kids signed out

32:46.600 --> 32:49.060
of the gated community
by the beach around 3:00 a.m.,

32:49.060 --> 32:50.440
but this kid, Max Shen,

32:50.440 --> 32:52.400
he didn't sign out
until 6:30.

32:52.400 --> 32:55.270
So he was in the vicinity around
the time Jessica was murdered.

32:55.270 --> 32:57.810
I tracked the family down to
a campground in Santa Paula.

32:57.810 --> 32:59.440
They're driving back now.

32:59.440 --> 33:02.480
His mom has agreed
to let him talk to us.

33:02.480 --> 33:04.850
Well, to you.

33:04.850 --> 33:06.940
She's a fan.

33:06.940 --> 33:14.940
♪♪

33:16.140 --> 33:21.690
♪♪

33:21.690 --> 33:24.060
We're trying to figure out
who killed Jessica Meyer.

33:24.060 --> 33:26.730
My mom says you're famous.

33:26.730 --> 33:27.940
I-I was.

33:27.940 --> 33:30.060
You were at Malibu Beach

33:30.060 --> 33:31.600
the night
before Jessica was killed.

33:31.600 --> 33:34.060
Do you have any information
about her death?

33:34.060 --> 33:35.310
- Answer her.
- It's okay.

33:35.310 --> 33:37.900
You're not in trouble.
I promise.

33:37.900 --> 33:39.850
Did you see Jessica?

33:39.850 --> 33:40.850
Yes.

33:40.850 --> 33:42.640
Yes, I saw her.

33:42.640 --> 33:47.640
♪♪

33:47.640 --> 33:50.900
Max, I need you to tell me
everything you remember.

33:50.900 --> 33:53.730
I was... pretty wasted.

33:53.730 --> 33:55.350
Then I guess I passed out,

33:55.350 --> 33:58.690
and then something woke me up
right before the sun was rising.

33:58.690 --> 33:59.980
And that's when I saw her.

33:59.980 --> 34:01.190
Jessica?

34:01.190 --> 34:02.980
She was covered in blood.

34:02.980 --> 34:04.640
She was dead.

34:07.230 --> 34:10.060
My name is Ben.

34:10.060 --> 34:11.770
I need to confess.

34:11.770 --> 34:13.639
What about this man?

34:13.639 --> 34:15.480
Have you seen him?

34:15.480 --> 34:17.139
Maya, you need to see this.
We're in the middle of something...

34:17.139 --> 34:18.139
Now!

34:19.560 --> 34:22.139
I've done a lot of bad things
in my life.

34:22.139 --> 34:24.230
Tha... That's the guy!
That's the guy that was at the beach!

34:24.230 --> 34:27.980
I've hurt myself and others...

34:27.980 --> 34:29.770
- What's going on?
- People I love.

34:29.770 --> 34:31.690
Ben Mitchell's confessing
his sins.

34:31.690 --> 34:33.270
What?

34:33.270 --> 34:34.690
I didn't stick up
for my little brother

34:34.690 --> 34:36.850
when he was getting beat up.

34:36.850 --> 34:38.810
I hit a dog when I was
driving home one night.

34:38.810 --> 34:40.900
I didn't stop.
I should've stopped.

34:40.900 --> 34:42.310
Get to the part
where you killed a woman.

34:42.310 --> 34:45.139
I should've been a better son.

34:45.139 --> 34:47.190
I'm sorry, Mom.

34:47.190 --> 34:48.980
There are no excuses.

34:48.980 --> 34:51.810
He's losing it.
Max, t-tell me what you saw.

34:51.810 --> 34:53.230
I was about to call 911,

34:53.230 --> 34:55.270
but then that guy
pulled up next to the beach.

34:55.270 --> 34:56.690
He started walking towards
the dead girl,

34:56.690 --> 34:57.850
and when he saw her,
he freaked out.

34:57.850 --> 34:59.230
Wait, Ben Mitchell arrived

34:59.230 --> 35:00.850
after Jessica was already dead?

35:00.850 --> 35:02.850
For sure.
So I got the hell out of there.

35:02.850 --> 35:04.850
I-I figured he'd call the cops,
leave me out of it.

35:04.850 --> 35:07.060
We need to call Ben,
tell him he's in the clear.

35:07.060 --> 35:09.730
My only hope
is that you'll forgive me

35:09.730 --> 35:10.980
for all the things I've done.

35:10.980 --> 35:14.560
I wanted to be better.

35:14.560 --> 35:16.940
There are so many ways
I could've been a better man.

35:19.480 --> 35:22.600
But I did not kill
Jessica Meyer.

35:22.600 --> 35:24.400
What?

35:24.400 --> 35:26.980
I was trying to help her
to get away from him.

35:26.980 --> 35:28.440
He's not answering. This guy's in trouble.
Now I have nothing.

35:28.440 --> 35:30.730
I need to get an APB
on Ben Mitchell.

35:34.640 --> 35:37.190
I'm just...

35:37.190 --> 35:38.560
so tired.

35:38.560 --> 35:40.310
You win.

35:42.600 --> 35:44.230
What is he doing?

35:45.480 --> 35:47.060
No.

35:47.060 --> 35:51.980
♪♪

35:51.980 --> 35:53.520
Oh, my God.

35:53.520 --> 35:54.850
No.

36:00.940 --> 36:02.190
Geez.

36:06.400 --> 36:11.060
♪♪

36:11.060 --> 36:12.900
Wasn't your fault.

36:14.270 --> 36:16.100
I know that's what
you're thinking.

36:18.600 --> 36:22.980
I should have gone easier
on him today or...

36:22.980 --> 36:27.230
tried harder to keep his name
out of the press.

36:27.230 --> 36:29.310
Ezra Wolf...

36:29.310 --> 36:30.810
He put Ben on blast.

36:32.690 --> 36:34.400
Destroyed that man.

36:35.730 --> 36:36.730
Not you.

36:36.730 --> 36:43.600
♪♪

36:43.600 --> 36:45.770
I've been such a bitch.

36:45.770 --> 36:48.600
We're not supposed to use
that word anymore.

36:48.600 --> 36:50.850
I don't hear you disagreeing.

36:50.850 --> 36:52.770
You were hurt.

36:52.770 --> 36:54.400
I get it.

36:54.400 --> 36:56.810
You know, I...

36:56.810 --> 37:00.140
I saw... what you went
through back then.

37:02.690 --> 37:05.100
But I never...

37:05.100 --> 37:07.140
I never felt it,
not until today...

37:11.350 --> 37:13.310
not until I saw
what happened to Ben.

37:17.730 --> 37:20.020
The world wrecked him.

37:23.440 --> 37:25.850
And you did what you had
to do to survive.

37:29.020 --> 37:31.140
And I don't get to be
angry about it.

37:33.440 --> 37:37.140
You forgive me?

37:37.140 --> 37:38.190
Come here.

37:40.020 --> 37:43.600
There's nothin' to forgive.

37:50.940 --> 37:53.850
Ezra Wolf is gonna obliterate
everything in his path

37:53.850 --> 37:56.440
to get Sevvy off.

37:56.440 --> 37:59.190
And he'll succeed
if we don't stop him.

37:59.190 --> 38:00.600
So, what do you want to do
about it?

38:00.600 --> 38:03.020
It's already in motion.

38:03.020 --> 38:04.600
I'm gonna out-wolf the Wolf.

38:21.140 --> 38:23.640
Ezra Wolf killed Ben Mitchell.

38:26.350 --> 38:28.690
Wolf likes to say
that we at the D.A.'s office

38:28.690 --> 38:30.940
rush to judgment,
when he is the one

38:30.940 --> 38:34.770
who publicly called
for Ben Mitchell's head.

38:34.770 --> 38:36.980
It's the same crap
he pulled eight years ago.

38:36.980 --> 38:40.020
Don't let him get away with it.

38:40.020 --> 38:42.230
It's too late to save Ben,

38:42.230 --> 38:45.350
but I am not gonna let the lives
of any more innocent people

38:45.350 --> 38:47.600
be destroyed by Ezra Wolf.

38:47.600 --> 38:49.770
I will not let him
twist the truth

38:49.770 --> 38:51.770
or play the race card.

38:51.770 --> 38:54.480
This case is not about race.

38:54.480 --> 38:56.940
It's about domestic violence.

38:56.940 --> 38:59.520
Sevvy Johnson killed
Jessica Meyer,

38:59.520 --> 39:01.730
and we are going to prove that.

39:01.730 --> 39:05.440
But you've heard enough
from Ezra Wolf and from me.

39:05.440 --> 39:07.310
It's time to let Jessica speak.

39:14.900 --> 39:18.100
He did it again.

39:19.770 --> 39:22.560
He gave me this when I said
I wasn't ready to leave

39:22.560 --> 39:25.190
Ray's dinner party last night.

39:25.190 --> 39:28.020
He gave me this
when we got home.

39:28.020 --> 39:29.640
I laughed too hard

39:29.640 --> 39:32.140
when Gabe made fun of Sevvy's
crappy golf swing.

39:35.060 --> 39:37.440
I'm such an idiot.

39:37.440 --> 39:38.980
My dad tried to warn me,

39:38.980 --> 39:40.940
and I should have listened.

39:40.940 --> 39:42.020
Dad?!

39:44.560 --> 39:45.980
Dad, are you seeing this?!

39:45.980 --> 39:48.190
I am not gonna wait around
for him to change

39:48.190 --> 39:50.900
and end up like her.
Dad!

39:50.900 --> 39:53.640
I'm taking these videos
to the police.

39:53.640 --> 39:55.810
Maya, is this enough
to arrest Sevvy?

39:57.270 --> 39:58.940
One at a time, please.

39:58.940 --> 40:01.270
I will answer
everybody's questions.

40:01.270 --> 40:03.560
I'm not going anywhere.
I promise.

40:03.560 --> 40:05.770
Do you feel the D.A.'s office
has enough to indict Sevvy?

40:05.770 --> 40:07.440
Sevvy Johnson killed Je...

40:10.520 --> 40:12.310
We can spin this.

40:12.310 --> 40:15.270
I don't know how yet, but I'll
figure it out. We can spin anything.

40:18.850 --> 40:20.440
Am I a terrible person?

40:23.270 --> 40:25.600
We're people of our time.

40:25.600 --> 40:28.400
And it's a terrible time.

40:28.400 --> 40:29.770
Hmm.

40:29.770 --> 40:34.980
♪♪

40:34.980 --> 40:40.230
♪♪

40:40.230 --> 40:42.020
This good?

40:43.690 --> 40:45.560
Yeah.

